Amazon S3 (Simple Storage Service)


Amazon S3 is a scalable object storage service used to store files, backups, images, logs, and application data. It provides high durability, security, and global availability.



What I Learned
How to create and manage S3 buckets

Uploading, downloading, and organizing objects

Understanding storage classes

Bucket permissions and policies

Versioning and lifecycle rules



Why S3 Matters


S3 is used for data storage, hosting static websites, backup solutions, logs, and even machine-learning datasets.















